Here are some arguments for removing de decidability lemmas on big numbers:
 -  this is dead code (never used within the CoLoR library);
 -  this is unrelated to rewriting theory and termination;
 -  if you think these lemmas are of general interest (beyond their non-usage within this library), they should be proposed for inclusion in the `bignums` library;
 -  the proofs make explicit reference to the `Int31` modules, that I would like to remove from Coq.
